9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 945, L.D. 1436, “An Act to Update and
10 Clarify Provisions Related to 9-1-1 Services”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 7 the following:
12 'Sec. 8. 25 MRSA §2921, sub-§2-B, as enacted by PL 2007, c. 68, §1, is amended
13 to read:
14 2-B. Cellular or wireless telecommunications service. "Cellular or wireless
15 telecommunications service" means commercial mobile service as defined in 47 United
16 States Code, Section 332(d), regardless of when payment is required for that service.'
17 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 12 and inserting the following:
18 'Sec. 12. 25 MRSA §2921, sub-§13, as amended by PL 2009, c. 400, §1 and
19 affected by §15, is further amended to read:
20 13. Prepaid wireless telecommunications service. "Prepaid wireless
21 telecommunications service" means a cellular or wireless telecommunications service that
22 allows a caller to dial 9-1-1 to access the E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system, which service must be paid
23 for in advance and is sold in predetermined units or dollars that declines with use in a
24 known amount.'
25 Amend the bill in section 23 in §2927-A in subsection 2 in paragraph B in the last line
26 (page 7, line 14 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "bill" the following: ', when
27 practicable. In circumstances in which separately showing the statewide 9-1-1 surcharge
28 on a customer's bill is not practicable, the local exchange telephone utility, cellular or
29 wireless telecommunications service provider or interconnected voice over Internet
30 protocol service provider must make the information regarding the amount of the 9-1-1
31 surcharge available to the customer in another manner'
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
